Play through the lines, between the lines, behind the lines, over the lines, along the lines and most especially mind the D. We’ve heard it all from the tacticians at this stage. But what about the man who designed these lines ? LINES is story 18 @dunnesstores , paying heed to the relationship between design and sport and the role sport’s great designer, the groundskeeper . Who is the local groundskeeper at your club? Tag the club , tell us your best groundskeeper story and we ll arrange for the groundskeeper jacket to be sent out to the best groundskeeper (designer) out there . #design #sport #storytelling @jamesoconnor_ @ucdgaa @officialgaa
I need a good use for all these LINES AND LINES AND LINES AND LINES ……. @ghostpoet #design #sport #lines

Here’s thinking of you Vince Linnane🙏🏼🙏🏼@kerrygaa_official @ballyduff_gaa_club @officialgaa . 🙏🏼🙏🏼 It was put to me many times along my journey that someone like me , a Gaelic footballer , a hurler , a sportsman, without design qualifications , had no business entering the world of “fashion” design. I saw it as an obvious move because sport cannot exist the same way without design , and design or fashion is not as influential without sport. Jerseys, balls, boots, stadia , you name it , all of these elements were designed for sport. The greatest sign of the connection between design and sport must be the playing pitch . Whatever sport you choose , design makes the playing pitch , and therefore the playing of that sport , possible . And one man (or woman) brings the playing pitch (and that sport) to life through design . LINES @dunnesstores recognises the groundskeeper as sports number 1 designer and presents the pitch as a made to measure piece of design . To my great friend Vince Linnane who kept Austin Stack Park hallowed for 30 years . #design #sport #lines

Good to catch up with the lads on @offtheball @shane_hannon01 last week. Good chat about design in sport, groundskeepers LINES @dunnesstores , and the football season so far. I have been surprised at the negativity towards Dublin’s form. Building a deep squad once more as far as I can see. Need to keep the mid 20s crew of Howard, Bugler, Murchan, Gannon , Comerford, P Small, MacMahon fit and driving it. Add Costelloe , Byrne, Basquels, the mainstays , the returnees and a newcomer like Killian O Gara and the numbers add serious competition in-house. O Gara can be a game changer for them at 14 particularly. Catch and kick can win them the AI. Thanks for the chat . Enjoy the season . #sport #GAA

New season story @dunnesstores . AICME looks at the nature of communication , how, through the Ogham alphabet, nature was once a communication platform, and how today with our multitude of communication platforms , good communication must appeal to basic human nature . Canopy prints , bark prints and Ogham characters do the communicating throughout the range . #design #storytelling #communication #nature @samardiff 🤌🏼
